  <title>Gio.SocketListener</title>
  <synopsis><code>
const Gio = imports.gi.Gio;

let socketListener = new Gio.SocketListener({
    <link xref='Gio.SocketListener-listen-backlog'>listen_backlog</link>: value,
});
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>A <link xref="Gio.SocketListener"/> is an object that keeps track of a set
of server sockets and helps you accept sockets from any of the
socket, either sync or async.</p>  <p>If you want to implement a network server, also look at <link xref="Gio.SocketService"/>
and <link xref="Gio.ThreadedSocketService"/> which are subclass of <link xref="Gio.SocketListener"/>
that makes this even easier.</p>
  <p>Since 2.22</p>
